Wash and dry produce.

Peel, trim, and halve @carrots{6%ounce} lengthwise; thinly slice into ¼-inch-thick
half-moons. Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}. Trim and halve
@zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Peel and
mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}. Roughly chop @fresh parsley{¼%ounce}.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with paper towels.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #medium pot{} (or
#large pot{} for 4 servings) over medium-high heat. Add carrots, onion,
a large pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
lightly browned, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add a drizzle of oil to #pot{}. Add chicken, zucchini, @Tunisian spice blend{1%tablespoon},
@cumin{1%teaspoon}, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until chicken is cooked through and veggies are tender, ~{4-6%minutes} more.

Stir garlic into pot with chicken and veggies. Cook, stirring, until fragrant,
~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in @diced tomatoes{14%ounce}, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, 2 1/2 cups
water (4 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and @sugar{¼%teaspoon} (½ tsp for 4).

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low. Simmer until flavors meld and stew is
slightly reduced, ~{6-8%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if
desired.

Divide stew between #bowls{}. Garnish with parsley and serve.